	   <tr><td colspan=2>Im very disappointed with my mage... I've played him to lvl 19, I use water pet, buff him with burnout, fire sheild, even melee to keep it alive and all that crap. I even have some realy nice INT items given to me by friends and people ive helped here & there. Yet I constantly get my ass handed to me. I hear people talk about soloing, Im lucky I can kill anything that gives me EXP anymore. Group you say? I never play my mage without my girlfriend who has a 19th lvl druid. Even she buffs my pet but it doesnt help. Im sick of Oasis and the over crowded aligator areas and orc highways. Right now Im in Rathelake near the Gnoll camp and after last nights fiasco I lost a level. I dont expect my pet to chop @#%^ in half in one hit, but the damn thing couldnt even agro the damn Gnoll ! Hell after making a pet, buffing it, I have no mana. Its gotta be me cause I read you guys talking about soloing when I wouldnt even think of trying it. H E L P ! WTF am I doing wrong?<br><br>but miss, but miss, but miss, but miss, but miss, you crush a gnoll shaman for 1 point of dmg, but miss, but miss, but miss, but miss, but miss........ETC...<br>&nbsp;<br> </td></tr>
