	   <tr><td colspan=2>lol i can think of about 5 things youre doing wrong.&nbsp;&nbsp;well i dont know much about soloing but at 19 i soloed in oasis EASILY.  it was great, actually... first real soloing id done that wasnt like lvl 10 crap.  first of all use earth while soloing... ALWAYS.  always make sure you have sow, too... just incase things go bad.  if you get too much of a pull like maybe a mummy jumps you back up and gate.  heal pet often, make a hotkey that is /pet report health.  when pet drops to maybe 75 hp start casting heal, not sure if thats renew elements or renew summoning at that lvl.  nuke the thing and try to time your hits so that they take dmg right after your pet roots.  rooting pisses the target off lots... so that will reduce lots of risk of them hitting you.  nuke it low hp if your pet gets to 30 hp and you are lom, prepare an escape.  if its goin ok and pet is standing lots of hits with little dmg then meditate so you can finish it with a nuke.  its best to have 80m or more whenever soloing.  it sounds like mage just isnt your class or sumptin cause i never had that much trouble soloing at those lvls, just dont try for more than blues unless you got some advantage.  suggestion to all lower lvl mages:  start soloing early!  get good at it at lower lvls, it only gets harder!  well off to go solo some stuff in OT... its actually easier than i thought it would be in there.<br>&nbsp;<br>Adalxx Diadem<br>~46 Elementalist<br>Mauteo Swiftfeet<br>~30 Monk<br>&lt;Currently Guildless&gt;<br>Xegony Server<br></td></tr>
